#Trees - **Binary Tree Inorder Traversal**

👉 Recursive solution: `O(n)` time and `O(n)` space (function call stack);

Here, We just traverse in such a way that after making left call we push the value at that point in the the vector and then make the right call. 

```
class Solution {
public:

    void traverse(TreeNode* root, vector<int> &ans)
    {
        if(!root)
            return;

        if(root->left) 
            traverse(root->left, ans);

        ans.push_back(root->val);  

        if(root->right)
            traverse(root->right, ans);
    }

    vector<int> inorderTraversal(TreeNode* root) 
    {
        vector<int> ans;

            traverse(root, ans);

        return ans;
    }
};
```

